cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the throughput performance of incremental relaying using energy harvesting relays, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on underlay cognitive radio networks, which are a type of wireless network. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the optimization of the power-splitting parameter of the energy harvesting relay, which involves control and optimization techniques. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly discuss security, but cognitive radio networks often involve spectrum sensing and sharing, which can have security implications. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not explicitly discuss multimedia, but the analysis of throughput performance may involve multimedia applications such as video streaming.
